# gametime — Cursor Rules

## Project
- Name: gametime
- Stack: Python, LightGBM, parquet, YAML config; MLB pregame ensemble (active), NBA (maintenance)
- Repo layout: `src/gametime/`, `configs/`, `subagent-prompts/`, workflow files at repo root

## Always Do First
- Read `agents.md`, `STANDARDS.md`, and `orchestrator-prompt.md` before any task
- Check Off-Limits Areas in `agents.md`
- Code-writing agents (AGENT_INFRA, AGENT_DATA, AGENT_BACKEND) must read `STANDARDS.md` before writing code
- Existing files → Existing Patterns. New files → Forward Standards.
- Check the task board in `orchestrator-prompt.md` before starting

## Commit & Branch Rules
- Commit format: `[AGENT_ID] TASK-XX: short description`
- Branch: `task/TASK-XX-short-desc` from `main`
- Merge target: `main` (no integration branch)
- Never commit to `main` directly
- Never commit secrets or `.env` files

## Standards
- `STANDARDS.md` is the source of truth for coding decisions
- Conflicts with `STANDARDS.md` → stop and flag, do not improvise
- MLB constraints: `docs/mlb_ensemble_roadmap.md`
- MLB ops: `docs/mlb_pregame_ops.md`

## Single Source of Truth
- `orchestrator-prompt.md` is the only backlog
- Worker prompts live in `subagent-prompts/` — not in archived docs
- `_archived/pre-reconcile/` is retired — do not use for task guidance

## Hard Constraints
- Do not break existing functionality
- Do not add dependencies without PR description note
- New MLB members: test decorrelation r < 0.94 vs all incumbents before merge
- Production blend: `use_stacking: false` unless human approves winner% tradeoff
- Val-only weight/stacker fitting; test 2025 is report-only holdout
